From gr|mbough @end|ng |rom gm@||@com  Wed Jul 30 16:14:42 2025
From: gr|mbough @end|ng |rom gm@||@com (Mike Smith)
Date: Wed, 30 Jul 2025 16:14:42 +0200
Subject: [Bioc-devel] chemmineob build failure due to missing zip lib
In-Reply-To: <675cde32-bde3-4f0d-84c4-37e6de1fb754@cs.ucr.edu>
References: <675cde32-bde3-4f0d-84c4-37e6de1fb754@cs.ucr.edu>
Message-ID: <CAGfgtYCjhhHD9xJii=08XgVu+Y2QDaN+wzMjG4H_JzkPuRynVQ@mail.gmail.com>

These errors look like they're actually coming from the OpenBabel library
itself (libopenbabel.a), rather than your package code.  That library is
looking for symbols defined in zlibbioc e.g. bioc_deflateEnd and it's not
finding them now you're linking against the regular zlib.  I think this
means someone needs to recompile the OpenBabel library installed on the
build machine so that it also uses the regular zlib, and then your changes
will be accurate.

Mike

On Wed, 30 Jul 2025 at 14:33, Kevin Horan <khoran at cs.ucr.edu> wrote:

